mecview_server 0.3.0
Michael Watzko <michael@watzko.de>
MECViewServer implementation in Rust

USAGE:
    mecview_server [OPTIONS]

FLAGS:
    -h, --help       Prints help information
    -V, --version    Prints version information

OPTIONS:
    -a, --algorithm <PATH>           The path to the algorithm
                                     configuration file [default:
                                     /etc/mecview/algorithm.json]
    -u, --use <ALGORITHM>            The algorithm to use
                                     [default: sample]
                                     [possible values: sample, external]
    -e, --environment-frame <PATH>   The path to the EnvironmentFrame
                                     to send to the Vehicles
    -v, --init-message <PATH>        The path to the InitMessage to
                                     send to a Vehicle
    -i, --interface <INTERFACE>      Sets the interface to listen on
                                     [default: 0.0.0.0]
    -l, --log <LEVEL>                Sets the log level of the server
                                     [possible values: trace, debug,
                                                       info, warn, err]
    -p, --port <NUMBER>              Sets the TCP listen port
                                     [default: 2000]
